# TS/JS Project Docs First

Shared rules cannot know every project's exact package names, test layers, schema library, or UI framework. Before broad TS/JS work, read the local docs that define those choices.

## Read first when relevant

- Foundation-hardening synthesis: `docs/FOUNDATION-HARDENING.md` or equivalent. (When the project has run a foundation-hardening pass, this is the single entry point that ties together lint + types + tests + docs.)
- Testing strategy: `docs/TESTING.md`, `TESTING.md`, or equivalent.
- Linting strategy: `docs/LINTING.md`, `eslint.config.*` comments, or equivalent.
- Typing strategy (TypeScript strict-flag rollout, per-workspace `tsc --noEmit` baseline): `docs/TYPING.md`, or equivalent.
- Coding standards: `docs/CODING-STANDARDS.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, or equivalent.
- Runtime validation/contracts: `docs/CONTRACTS-VALIDATION-STRATEGY.md` (project-canonical validation strategy; this repo's v2.0 commits to Zod v4 per `docs/rfcs/0003-validation-library-adoption.md`), package README files, or equivalent.
- Module-README standard: `docs/DOCS-README-STANDARDS.md`, or equivalent.
- Accessibility/UI rules: `docs/DEVELOPMENT-ACCESSIBILITY.md`, design-system docs, or equivalent.
- Architecture direction: `docs/PLATFORM-ARCHITECTURE.md`, architecture decision records, or equivalent.

## Rules

- Prefer project-local docs over generic assumptions when they conflict with this shared package.
- If a referenced doc is absent, proceed with the generic rule and ask only for values that are necessary for the task.
- Do not invent package names, container names, validation libraries, test commands, route conventions, or design-system primitives.
- When a local doc says a convention is mandatory, treat it as a guardrail for the session.

## Anti-patterns

- adding a route without checking the project's test-layer mapping
- changing lint strictness without reading lint docs
- introducing or switching schema libraries (Zod, Valibot, TypeBox, Fastify schemas, hand-rolled) without checking the project-local validation strategy doc — this repo's choice is recorded in `docs/CONTRACTS-VALIDATION-STRATEGY.md` v2.0 (Zod v4) + `docs/rfcs/0003-validation-library-adoption.md`; mixing libraries inside the same codebase is explicitly forbidden by RFC-0003 Decision A
- building UI without checking accessibility and design-system guidance
